  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 200°C (392°F). Season beef with salt and pepper.",
    "Heat butter in a pan over medium heat. Add onions and garlic; cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add beef slices and brown on all sides. Remove from pan.",
    "In the same pan, melt nutmeg and sauté for another minute.",
    "Return beef to the pan along with white wine. Bring to a simmer, then reduce heat to low and cook until liquid is mostly absorbed.",
    "Stir in heavy cream, soy sauce, nutritional yeast, and grated Parmesan cheese; simmer until mixture thickens.",
    "Top with optional pecorino cheese before serving. Garnish with fresh herbs if desired.",
    "Serve hot as a main course or side dish."
  ],
